<task id="AIPU2-087" project="Spaarke AI Platform Unification R2">
  <metadata>
    <title>Build EntityInfoWidget for Context Pane</title>
    <phase>4D</phase>
    <tags>frontend, widgets, entity</tags>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <dependencies>AIPU2-073</dependencies>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>
  <prompt>
    During the loading and early active-chat stages, the Context pane shows information about
    the entity currently in scope (e.g., a legal matter: matter name, client, status, key dates,
    budget). This gives users immediate context without requiring a chat turn. EntityInfoWidget
    implements ContextWidget and loads entity detail from Dataverse context passed via the
    context_update event payload. It must update reactively when the entity context changes
    (e.g., user navigates to a different matter record).
  </prompt>
  <role>Frontend developer with React 19, Fluent v9, and Dataverse context integration experience.</role>
  <goal>
    Entity information (matter name, client, status, key dates, budget) displays in the Context
    pane during entity-info stage. Widget updates when entity context changes. Registered in
    ContextWidgetRegistry.
  </goal>
  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>
  <steps>
    <step>Read ADR-021 to confirm Fluent v9 component and token requirements.</step>
    <step>Create src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Widgets/src/widgets/context/EntityInfoWidget.tsx implementing ContextWidget.</step>
    <step>Define EntityInfoData type: { entityType: string; entityId: string; displayName: string; clientName?: string; status?: string; keyDates?: KeyDate[]; budget?: BudgetSummary; customFields?: Record&lt;string, string&gt; }.</step>
    <step>Render entity information using Fluent v9 layout: displayName as heading, status as Badge, key dates as a compact list, budget as a progress bar (spent vs. total) if present, customFields as a definition list.</step>
    <step>Subscribe to additional context_update events within the widget using usePaneEvent on the 'context' channel — when a new entity-info event arrives with a different entityId, update the displayed data reactively.</step>
    <step>Show a Fluent v9 Skeleton loading state while entity data is being fetched if the initial payload is partial.</step>
    <step>Handle missing optional fields gracefully — absent fields are simply not rendered (no empty rows).</step>
    <step>Register EntityInfoWidget in ContextWidgetRegistry.</step>
    <step>Write unit tests: entity fields render correctly; missing optional fields produce no empty rows; entityId change updates displayed data.</step>
  </steps>
  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion>Entity display name, client, status, key dates, and budget render correctly using Fluent v9 components.</criterion>
    <criterion>Missing optional fields are omitted — no empty rows or null labels.</criterion>
    <criterion>Widget updates reactively when a new context_update event with a different entityId arrives.</criterion>
    <criterion>Skeleton loading state renders while entity data is incomplete.</criterion>
    <criterion>Widget registered in ContextWidgetRegistry and renders in ContextPaneController during entity-info stage.</criterion>
    <criterion>No hard-coded colors — all styling uses Fluent v9 design tokens (ADR-021).</criterion>
    <criterion>Unit tests for field rendering, optional omission, and reactive update pass.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
